2
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:29,930
[To Dear Myself]

3
00:01:30,740 --> 00:01:34,240
[Episode 41]

4
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:36,130
He Mu, do you love me?

5
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:46,880
I feel a bit unwell today so I'm going home to rest now.

6
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:57,580
We welcome you to come next time!

7
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:17,140
[Lei Haowen]

8
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,050
[Share your location.]

9
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,150
Lixing, where is the soy sauce?

10
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:47,030
In the cupboard. Look for it yourself.

11
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:09,160
Lixing,

12
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,590
are there bigger bowls?

13
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:13,560
See for yourself.

14
00:03:43,070 --> 00:03:46,420
Stop working, we're having dinner soon.

15
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,010
Time to eat!

16
00:03:57,010 --> 00:03:58,940
It's ready?

17
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:02,420
Come on, Sushan, let's eat.

18
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:05,450
You are hungry, right?

19
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:10,180
Okay. Let's go and eat.

20
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:13,460
Here.

21
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,600
Sit tight, okay?

22
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:19,520
Wait a minute. Haven't I told you that

23
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:24,180
you need to wipe your hands clean before dinner? Otherwise, there will be germs. Did you forget?

24
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,950
Here. Let me wipe them for you, okay?

25
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:30,600
The other one.

26
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,370
All right, they are clean now. Eat.

27
00:04:36,370 --> 00:04:39,400
Here, I just made some dishes with whatever I could find. Try the noodles.

28
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:43,030
How is it?

29
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:46,200
These are the best tasting noodles I've ever had!

30
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,050
- Really? 
 - Right?

31
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:50,580
Best tasting? Then eat more, okay?

32
00:04:50,580 --> 00:04:52,540
You should try it, too.

33
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,050
This is the life I want the most.

34
00:05:03,050 --> 00:05:08,200
I work hard out there while you stay home to take care of the house chores and children.

35
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:14,470
Every day, when I come home, I can see Sushan's adorable smile,

36
00:05:14,470 --> 00:05:16,780
and there will be a hot bowl of noodles to eat.

37
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:24,770
Tomorrow's the weekend, yes?

38
00:05:24,770 --> 00:05:26,120
You don't have any plans, right?

39
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:28,790
If you don't,

40
00:05:28,790 --> 00:05:32,100
then help me take Sushan to training class in the morning.

41
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,260
I have some things to take care of at work.

42
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,900
I'll probably be at the company all day.

43
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,300
Okay.

44
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:44,650
The cleaning lady will also come in the afternoon. You should come and take a look.

45
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:54,380
Also, kids are usually not used to the food and water in a foreign country.

46
00:05:54,380 --> 00:06:00,170
If you walk past a pharmacy, you should buy some children's medication. I'm afraid she might catch a cold or get sick.

47
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:05,740
Here.

48
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,870
Eat some vegetables, okay?

49
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,640
I thought you'd never talk to me again.

50
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:25,300
I don't want to talk to you,

51
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,140
but I can't resist the temptation of large intestines.

52
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:32,430
I also wanted to cut off ties with you

53
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:36,340
but then I thought about it and I can't just lose like this.

54
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:38,770
Then, what do you want to do?

55
00:06:41,550 --> 00:06:46,340
Aren't you still not married yet? Even if you are married,

56
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:49,290
isn't there the possibility of divorce?

57
00:06:49,290 --> 00:06:51,220
Even if you don't get a divorce,

58
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:55,940
if you want to have an extramarital affair, then wouldn't I still have hope?

59
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,700
Lei Haowen,

60
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:07,050
if you still want to be friends with me, then give up on those ideas right now.

61
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:10,490
Otherwise, I'll leave right now and never see you again.

62
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:12,630
Hey, hey, hey.

63
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:17,310
There's no "if," okay? Don't get angry.

64
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:19,650
Sit, sit, sit.

65
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:22,000
They're all staring.

66
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,990
Sit down.

67
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:36,570
You need to give me some time, all right?

68
00:07:36,570 --> 00:07:40,490
You have to let my heart slowly die.

69
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:44,370
We can only be friends.

70
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:48,250
Friends. Let's drink.

71
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:56,280
Here. Your favorite, large intestines.

72
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,650
Lei Haowen,

73
00:08:16,650 --> 00:08:21,220
if I asked to borrow ¥5,000,000 from you, would you?

74
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:23,800
That's with the assumption that you have that much money.

75
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,490
I'd lend it to you.

76
00:08:29,170 --> 00:08:30,860
I might not be able to return it.

77
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:32,550
I'll still lend it to you.

78
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:34,550
Aren't you going to ask what I'm going to do with it?

79
00:08:34,550 --> 00:08:36,340
Nope.

80
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:38,170
Aren't you afraid that I'll use it to do bad things?

81
00:08:38,170 --> 00:08:40,760
Don't I know you well?

82
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:43,710
Thank you.

83
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:45,150
You're welcome.

84
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:51,210
With your brain, besides buying purses and clothes, what else would you possibly save for?

85
00:08:51,210 --> 00:08:53,560
Hey, don't, don't! There you go again!

86
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:55,420
Why are you so agitated?

87
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:57,340
It's fine. Just a couple, a couple arguing.

88
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:59,060
Stop talking!

89
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:03,210
Pick up the phone. Pick up the phone.

90
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:13,880
Did you guys get into an argument?

91
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,790
None of your business.

92
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,980
Right, right. None of my business.

93
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:24,580
If you could really give me ¥5,000,000, then that would be great.

94
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:27,240
Why do you want that much money?

95
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:31,080
It's not me. It's Li Siyu, that prodigal woman.

96
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,800
Why does she want that much money?

97
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:37,930
Lately, she's been working on a project and needs investments. She's been so anxious, she's about to go crazy soon.

98
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:47,760
Why are they all blowing into our faces?

99
00:09:49,810 --> 00:09:52,080
Look who's here.

100
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,340
Mommy!

101
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,070
Did you have a good time with your daddy today?

102
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:08,970
Yes!

103
00:10:10,290 --> 00:10:12,560
I have something to say to you.

104
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:17,600
I happen to have something to say to you as well.

105
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:26,050
Be careful.

106
00:10:26,050 --> 00:10:27,620
Okay.

107
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:35,670
Sister Siyu wants to start a business again.

108
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:41,500
And it's in collaboration with your lab. Is this reliable?

109
00:10:44,590 --> 00:10:46,990
What do you mean by reliable?

110
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:52,220
Will the experiment be successful?

111
00:10:54,080 --> 00:11:00,090
There's... a 0.01% chance.

112
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:04,700
That low?

113
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:08,280
Then Sister Siyu is really risking too much.

114
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,150
I understand her.

115
00:11:14,930 --> 00:11:19,320
The risk is worth it if you can do the thing you like.

116
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:24,190
This is something that you want to do as well?

117
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:25,730
Yes.

118
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:33,480
After graduating from graduate school, I wanted to continue working in research

119
00:11:34,850 --> 00:11:40,100
but my rational side told me that I should get a better job.

120
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:43,720
That way I didn't have to worry about anything in this lifetime.

121
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:46,390
That's why I entered my old workplace.

122
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:50,660
You spent ten years there.

123
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,700
To be honest, in those ten years,

124
00:11:57,520 --> 00:12:00,980
I had many thoughts of changing my career,

125
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:07,350
but I was afraid to start over. I just thought about it. That's it.

126
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:15,360
Then, did your wish come true now?

127
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:19,310
Of course.

128
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:25,490
Right now, even though I have a very low salary, every day is very fulfilling.

129
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:30,240
Although the experiment keeps failing,

130
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:35,410
but to a researcher, failing is very normal.

131
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:44,230
Then what if... in the end, you still fail?

132
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,260
What does "the end" mean?

133
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:51,110
Success is the only ending.

134
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:55,960
As long as we haven't succeeded, it is not the end.

135
00:12:57,320 --> 00:13:01,040
You were never like this before. You've always wanted stability.

136
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:07,740
That's because when I was young, my living conditions weren't well. I couldn't afford to make mistakes.

137
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:12,270
So every step I took, I had to be sure.

138
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,810
However, after experiencing everything that's happened in the past two years,

139
00:13:16,810 --> 00:13:18,990
I found that

140
00:13:18,990 --> 00:13:21,670
life is full of unforeseen circumstances.

141
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:24,810
No matter how careful and cautious you are,

142
00:13:24,810 --> 00:13:28,040
in the end, you may still fall into a pit.

143
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:34,710
So, instead of being overly cautious and indecisive, I would rather choose something I like

144
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:37,250
and put my heart and soul into it.

145
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,650
You've changed.

146
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,440
You have also changed.

147
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:54,580
In the past, we would never discuss things like this.

148
00:13:56,290 --> 00:13:58,570
You never asked either.

149
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:07,220
I would have never thought that we could talk like this after getting divorced.

150
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:13,380
It looks like being divorced is better.

151
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,950
I've thought about it.

152
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:53,950
It's better if I return this to you.

153
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:16,560
Are you certain?

154
00:15:17,930 --> 00:15:19,830
Of what?

155
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:22,210
Yuwei told me already.

156
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:36,380
Then after you go to Europe with him, will you continue to work?

157
00:15:39,490 --> 00:15:45,390
His company's benefits are very good. Once we're there, I won't have to work.

158
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:57,490
Don't worry. He treats Yuwei and I very well

159
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:09,470
Zhizhi, I'm actually pretty happy.

160
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:14,450
I don't have money nor many capabilities.

161
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:20,860
If you were with me, you'd have to keep working. That would be too hard for you.

162
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,620
But Sushan's dad is completely different.

163
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:27,880
With him,

164
00:16:28,610 --> 00:16:31,160
you can live without worries.

165
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:34,360
That's pretty good.

166
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:39,340
Liu Yang,

167
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:47,380
I have never looked down on the fact that you were poor.

168
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,360
I know.

169
00:16:57,030 --> 00:17:02,120
Zhizhi, you are an amazing wife.

170
00:17:02,660 --> 00:17:05,390
The best wife on this Earth.

171
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,220
It is I who is not worthy of you.

172
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:20,530
 Timing & Subtitles by My Dear Myself Team @Viki.com 

173
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,360
Honestly,

174
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:32,170
I like working.

175
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:36,980
If you like it, then go do it.

176
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:39,470
Don't let yourself regret anything.

177
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:57,990
You should keep this. I owed it to you.

178
00:18:19,010 --> 00:18:21,040
I'm back.

179
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:28,060
What are you doing?

180
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:36,770
What is going on?

181
00:18:36,770 --> 00:18:38,600
I looked into it already.

182
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:41,590
It's better to sell these bags on Huafer. 
 (T/N: a Chinese website used to sell specifically high-quality items)

183
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:44,450
You get much more money than secondhand shops.

184
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:52,840
Xiaoling, all of these are your beloved items.

185
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:58,250
I'm most annoyed when I see you like this. Can't you just be cool about it?

186
00:18:59,540 --> 00:19:03,440
Fine. After I make money, I'll buy them all back for you.

187
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,400
- You need to get more than just them for me! 
 - I'll buy you twice as many things!

188
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,220
Deal!

189
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,610
Answer the phone.

190
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:22,980
Hello?

191
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:25,860
Xiaoling, let's have dinner together.

192
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:29,420
Let's go to your favorite French restaurant.

193
00:19:29,420 --> 00:19:31,760
Today is not a date night though.

194
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:36,610
Oh... One of my clients suddenly had something come up, so I have free time now.

195
00:19:36,610 --> 00:19:38,920
So we can meet up.

196
00:19:39,410 --> 00:19:41,140
I have a guest at my house.

197
00:19:41,140 --> 00:19:42,730
I can't go.

198
00:19:42,730 --> 00:19:47,110
Can you see if you can make time?

199
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:49,040
We didn't meet last week either.

200
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:52,530
I cannot make time. She's leaving Shanghai tomorrow.

201
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:58,320
Okay. I hope you two have fun then.

202
00:20:06,250 --> 00:20:08,520
Did you two get into an argument?

203
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,300
It would be great if we actually argued.

204
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:13,390
Then what happened?

205
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:20,180
I asked to borrow money from him. Not only did he say no, but he also went off on a long lecture.

206
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:30,940
Xiaoling, in regards to lending money, people do it out of kindness but are not obligated to do it.

207
00:20:30,940 --> 00:20:35,650
I think that He Mu's actions were not unreasonable.

208
00:20:35,650 --> 00:20:38,900
But you're my older sister, and it was me who asked.

209
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,590
So what?

210
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:44,890
First of all, the two of you are not yet married. Second of all, even if you were married,

211
00:20:44,890 --> 00:20:47,330
he still has no obligation to help me.

212
00:20:47,330 --> 00:20:49,970
He's so boring. Why would I marry him?

213
00:20:49,970 --> 00:20:54,090
It's because he is rich. However, now that I need money,

214
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:57,160
not only does he do nothing, but he—

215
00:20:58,030 --> 00:21:00,270
Why would I get married to him?

216
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:11,590
Xiaoling, break up with He Mu.

217
00:21:12,650 --> 00:21:17,230
Not because he won't lend me money but because of what you just said.

218
00:21:17,230 --> 00:21:18,850
What did I just say?

219
00:21:18,850 --> 00:21:22,430
You were going to marry him for money.

220
00:21:22,430 --> 00:21:24,100
What's wrong with that?

221
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:25,980
There's nothing wrong with that.

222
00:21:25,980 --> 00:21:30,320
However, a happy marriage comes from love, not from money.

223
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,830
You still believe in love?

224
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,200
I've always believed in it.

225
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:37,560
You and Chen Yiming loved each other so much, but you two still broke up, didn't you?

226
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:45,070
Chen Yiming and I broke up because we didn't love each other enough.

227
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:48,930
The two of you were engaged yet you two didn't love each other enough?

228
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:55,540
Perhaps our love was just enough to get engaged.

229
00:21:56,330 --> 00:22:00,580
Now that I think about it, when two people are truly together,

230
00:22:00,580 --> 00:22:03,590
they need to sacrifice bits of themselves,

231
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:08,660
and, more importantly, they must be brave enough to face life's pressures.

232
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:12,470
But I wasn't ready for any of that.

233
00:22:13,780 --> 00:22:16,520
When did you figure all of these things out?

234
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:22,970
After Laidianle failed.

235
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:30,360
On that day, I looked at myself in the mirror.

236
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:37,410
I was anxious, impetuous, and paranoid.

237
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:42,670
I wanted instant success and was defiant.

238
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:48,360
Even I loathed that woman.

239
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:50,840
What right do I have to ask someone else to love me?

240
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,870
Then, what about now?

241
00:22:54,970 --> 00:23:01,030
Now... Don't you think I'm very cute?

242
00:23:04,870 --> 00:23:07,050
Then...

243
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:10,940
If another person appears in your life, how would you love him?

244
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:18,360
I definitely would still put my heart and soul into loving him.

245
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:23,090
You have already "hit a wall causing your head to bleed",  yet you still don't know to change. (T/N: already been brutally hurt once before by someone who does not reciprocate) 

246
00:23:23,090 --> 00:23:25,990
Since my head already bled, then it's even more important that I don't change.

247
00:23:25,990 --> 00:23:31,240
What if I hit the wall a few more times and it falls? Then I win!

248
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:33,270
I hope you will be happy.

249
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:38,430
Xiaoling, I also wish that you will be happy.

250
00:23:38,430 --> 00:23:41,220
Don't marry someone because of money.

251
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:44,080
If you only have love, then you will starve to death.

252
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:47,110
If you only have love then you will starve to death!

253
00:23:47,110 --> 00:23:48,080
Let go.

254
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,680
I can't communicate with you.

255
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:52,510
